data.title: Full Interview: Mark Woodforde, What's It Like To Be A Tennis Champion
data.meta_description: On working with John McEnroe and more!
data.text:
17-time Grand Slam champion and one half of the 'Woodies' Mark Woodforde joins Bec & Soda on SAFM to talk What's It Like To be a tennis champion!

Listen now:

South Australian and former alumni of Marion High School talks about his incredible career of tennis including taking home 12 major mens doubles titles, 6 Wimbeldon titles, 2 Australian Opens, 1 French Open and 67 ATP titles!

He also dishes about working with John McEnroe and the Hollywood stars that came out to see him play--Dustin Hoffman in the locker room, Chevy Chase as ball boy at practice!

Rebecca 'Bec' Morse and Mark 'Soda' Soderstrom also uncover a bit of a crush Mark Woodforde had on a tennis partner...making him blush mid-interview!
